{"word":"κορέννυμι","slug":"κορέννυμι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κορέννυμι</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>κεκορηώς</el>, epic <a href='S:participle'>part.</a> <a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> with <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> sense\n<p/><i>to sate, satiate, satisfy</i>, <el>τινα</el> <b><a href='S:Theognis'>Theogn.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>: <i>to fill</i> one <i>with</i> a thing, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>; also <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> rei, <i>to fill full of</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a> <i>to satisfy oneself, have one's fill</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <el>ἐκορέσσατο φορβῆς</el> <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:participle'>part.</a>, <el>κλαίουσα κορέσσατο</el> <i>she had her fill</i> of weeping, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>: —<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be satiated</i>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>; rarely <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a> rei, <el>πλούτωι κεκορημένος</el> <b><a href='S:Theognis'>Theogn.</a></b>; <el>ὕβρι</el> <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/>"}]}